para.para: CMSIS Cortex-M4 Device Peripheral Access Layer Header File. This file contains all the peripheral register's definitions, bits definitions and memory mapping for STM32F4xx devices.

listitem.para: Comment the line below if you will not use the peripherals drivers. In this case, these drivers will not be included and the application code will be based on direct access to peripherals registers.
STM32F4XX Standard Peripherals Library version number V1.8.0.

section.title: Ayrıntılı tanımlama
section.para: CMSIS Cortex-M4 Device Peripheral Access Layer Header File. This file contains all the peripheral register's definitions, bits definitions and memory mapping for STM32F4xx devices.

Yazar
MCD Application Team
Sürüm
V1.8.1
Tarih
27-January-2022
The file is the unique include file that the application programmer is using in the C source code, usually in main.c. This file contains:
Configuration section that allows to select:
The device used in the target application
To use or not the peripherals drivers in application code(i.e. code will be based on direct access to peripherals registers rather than drivers API), this option is controlled by "#define USE_STDPERIPH_DRIVER"
To change few application-specific parameters such as the HSE crystal frequency
Data structures and the address mapping for all peripherals
Peripherals registers declarations and bits definition
Macros to access peripherals registers hardware
